9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 337, L.D. 823, “An Act to Establish a
10 Grant Program to Provide for Statewide and Equitable Access to Experiential Science,
11 Technology, Engineering and Mathematics Competition Programs”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in §15312 in subsection 1 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 6 in
13 L.D.) by striking out the following: "is going" and inserting the following: 'intends'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in §15312 in subsection 3 in paragraph B in the first line
15 (page 1, line 39 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "and private schools"
16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment provides that an organization that receives a competitive grant for
2200 statewide experiential science, technology, engineering and mathematics competition
2211 programs does not need to make the program available to students from private schools and
2222 that to receive a grant an organization must demonstrate that it intends to use the funds for
2233 a statewide experiential competition program.
2244 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2255 (See attached)
